The paper focuses on the integration of open data statistics with historical events to help users interpret the data. This involves the use of interactive visualizations and a timeline of thematically appropriate historical events from Wikipedia. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it deals with the design and evaluation of a user interface. It also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as users need to search for related events and details on Wikipedia. The paper may also fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, as the use of open data statistics and historical events may have implications for security and privacy. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, as it involves the exploration of trends and relationships in data. Finally, the paper may be related to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category, as it involves the integration of different sources of data.
